18// Helper functions for extracting fields from encoded instructions.
19// InsnType must either be integral or an APInt-like object that must:
20// * Have a static const max_size_in_bits equal to the number of bits in the
21// encoding.
22// * be default-constructible and copy-constructible
23// * be constructible from a uint64_t
24// * be constructible from an APInt (this can be private)
25// * Support getBitsSet(loBit, hiBit)
26// * be convertible to uint64_t
27// * Support the ~, &, ==, !=, and |= operators with other objects of the same type
28// * Support shift (<<, >>) with signed and unsigned integers on the RHS
29// * Support put (<<) to raw_ostream&
30template <typename InsnType>
31#if defined(_MSC_VER) && !defined(__clang__)
32__declspec(noinline)
33#endif
34static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
35 unsigned numBits, std::true_type) {
36 assert(startBit + numBits <= 64 && "Cannot support >64-bit extractions!");
37 assert(startBit + numBits <= (sizeof(InsnType) * 8) &&
38 "Instruction field out of bounds!");
39 InsnType fieldMask;
40 if (numBits == sizeof(InsnType) * 8)
41 fieldMask = (InsnType)(-1LL);
42 else
43 fieldMask = (((InsnType)1 << numBits) - 1) << startBit;
44 return (insn & fieldMask) >> startBit;
45}
46
47template <typename InsnType>
48static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
49 unsigned numBits, std::false_type) {
50 assert(startBit + numBits <= InsnType::max_size_in_bits && "Instruction field out of bounds!");
51 InsnType fieldMask = InsnType::getBitsSet(0, numBits);
52 return (insn >> startBit) & fieldMask;
53}
54
55template <typename InsnType>
56static InsnType fieldFromInstruction(InsnType insn, unsigned startBit,
57 unsigned numBits) {
58 return fieldFromInstruction(insn, startBit, numBits, std::is_integral<InsnType>());
59}

3893
3894static bool checkDecoderPredicate(unsigned Idx, const FeatureBitset &Bits) {
3895 switch (Idx) {
3896 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid index!");
3897 case 0:
3898 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtC]);
3899 case 1:
3900 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtC] && !Bits[RISCV::FeatureNoRVCHints]);
3901 case 2:
3902 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtC] && Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtD]);
3903 case 3:
3904 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtC] && Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3905 case 4:
3906 return (Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3907 case 5:
3908 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtV]);
3909 case 6:
3910 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtZvlsseg]);
3911 case 7:
3912 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZfh]);
3913 case 8:
3914 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtF]);
3915 case 9:
3916 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureStdExtD]);
3917 case 10:
3918 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbp]);
3919 case 11:
3920 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbs]);
3921 case 12:
3922 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbb]);
3923 case 13:
3924 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbm] && Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3925 case 14:
3926 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbr]);
3927 case 15:
3928 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbr] && Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3929 case 16:
3930 return ((Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbb] || Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbp]));
3931 case 17:
3932 return ((Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbb] || Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbp]) && !Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3933 case 18:
3934 return ((Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbb] || Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbp]) && Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3935 case 19:
3936 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbt]);
3937 case 20:
3938 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZba] && Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3939 case 21:
3940 return (Bits[RISCV::FeatureExtZbs] && Bits[RISCV::Feature64Bit]);
3941 case 22:

4972
4973template <typename InsnType>
4974static DecodeStatus decodeInstruction(const uint8_t DecodeTable[], MCInst &MI,
4975 InsnType insn, uint64_t Address,
4976 const void *DisAsm,
4977 const MCSubtargetInfo &STI) {
4978 const FeatureBitset &Bits = STI.getFeatureBits();
4979
4980 const uint8_t *Ptr = DecodeTable;
4981 InsnType CurFieldValue = 0;
4982 DecodeStatus S = MCDisassembler::Success;
4983 while (true) {
4984 ptrdiff_t Loc = Ptr - DecodeTable;
4985 switch (*Ptr) {
4986 default:
4987 errs() << Loc << ": Unexpected decode table opcode!\n";
4988 return MCDisassembler::Fail;
4989 case MCD::OPC_ExtractField: {
4990 unsigned Start = *++Ptr;
4991 unsigned Len = *++Ptr;
4992 ++Ptr;
4993 CurFieldValue = fieldFromInstruction(insn, Start, Len);
4994 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_ExtractField(" << Start << ", "
4995 << Len << "): " << CurFieldValue << "\n");
4996 break;
4997 }
4998 case MCD::OPC_FilterValue: {
4999 // Decode the field value.
5000 unsigned Len;
5001 InsnType Val = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
5002 Ptr += Len;
5003 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
5004 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
5005 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
5006 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
5007
5008 // Perform the filter operation.
5009 if (Val != CurFieldValue)
5010 Ptr += NumToSkip;
5011 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_FilterValue(" << Val << ", " << NumToSkip
5012 << "): " << ((Val != CurFieldValue) ? "FAIL:" : "PASS:")
5013 << " continuing at " << (Ptr - DecodeTable) << "\n");
5014
5015 break;
5016 }
5017 case MCD::OPC_CheckField: {
5018 unsigned Start = *++Ptr;
5019 unsigned Len = *++Ptr;
5020 InsnType FieldValue = fieldFromInstruction(insn, Start, Len);
5021 // Decode the field value.
5022 InsnType ExpectedValue = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
5023 Ptr += Len;
5024 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
5025 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
5026 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
5027 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
5028
5029 // If the actual and expected values don't match, skip.
5030 if (ExpectedValue != FieldValue)
5031 Ptr += NumToSkip;
5032 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_CheckField(" << Start << ", "
5033 << Len << ", " << ExpectedValue << ", " << NumToSkip
5034 << "): FieldValue = " << FieldValue << ", ExpectedValue = "
5035 << ExpectedValue << ": "
5036 << ((ExpectedValue == FieldValue) ? "PASS\n" : "FAIL\n"));
5037 break;
5038 }
5039 case MCD::OPC_CheckPredicate: {
5040 unsigned Len;
5041 // Decode the Predicate Index value.
5042 unsigned PIdx = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
5043 Ptr += Len;
5044 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
5045 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
5046 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
5047 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
5048 // Check the predicate.
5049 bool Pred;
5050 if (!(Pred = checkDecoderPredicate(PIdx, Bits)))
5051 Ptr += NumToSkip;
5052 (void)Pred;
5053 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_CheckPredicate(" << PIdx << "): "
5054 << (Pred ? "PASS\n" : "FAIL\n"));
5055
5056 break;
5057 }
5058 case MCD::OPC_Decode: {
5059 unsigned Len;
5060 // Decode the Opcode value.
5061 unsigned Opc = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
5062 Ptr += Len;
5063 unsigned DecodeIdx = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
5064 Ptr += Len;
5065
5066 MI.clear();
5067 MI.setOpcode(Opc);
5068 bool DecodeComplete;
5069 S = decodeToMCInst(S, DecodeIdx, insn, MI, Address, DisAsm, DecodeComplete);
5070 assert(DecodeComplete);
5071
5072 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_Decode: opcode " << Opc
5073 << ", using decoder " << DecodeIdx << ": "
5074 << (S != MCDisassembler::Fail ? "PASS" : "FAIL") << "\n");
5075 return S;
5076 }
5077 case MCD::OPC_TryDecode: {
5078 unsigned Len;
5079 // Decode the Opcode value.
5080 unsigned Opc = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
5081 Ptr += Len;
5082 unsigned DecodeIdx = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
5083 Ptr += Len;
5084 // NumToSkip is a plain 24-bit integer.
5085 unsigned NumToSkip = *Ptr++;
5086 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 8;
5087 NumToSkip |= (*Ptr++) << 16;
5088
5089 // Perform the decode operation.
5090 MCInst TmpMI;
5091 TmpMI.setOpcode(Opc);
5092 bool DecodeComplete;
5093 S = decodeToMCInst(S, DecodeIdx, insn, TmpMI, Address, DisAsm, DecodeComplete);
5094 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_TryDecode: opcode " << Opc
5095 << ", using decoder " << DecodeIdx << ": ");
5096
5097 if (DecodeComplete) {
5098 // Decoding complete.
5099 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (S != MCDisassembler::Fail ? "PASS" : "FAIL") << "\n");
5100 MI = TmpMI;
5101 return S;
5102 } else {
5103 assert(S == MCDisassembler::Fail);
5104 // If the decoding was incomplete, skip.
5105 Ptr += NumToSkip;
5106 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "FAIL: continuing at " << (Ptr - DecodeTable) << "\n");
5107 // Reset decode status. This also drops a SoftFail status that could be
5108 // set before the decode attempt.
5109 S = MCDisassembler::Success;
5110 }
5111 break;
5112 }
5113 case MCD::OPC_SoftFail: {
5114 // Decode the mask values.
5115 unsigned Len;
5116 InsnType PositiveMask = decodeULEB128(++Ptr, &Len);
5117 Ptr += Len;
5118 InsnType NegativeMask = decodeULEB128(Ptr, &Len);
5119 Ptr += Len;
5120 bool Fail = (insn & PositiveMask) || (~insn & NegativeMask);
5121 if (Fail)
5122 S = MCDisassembler::SoftFail;
5123 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_SoftFail: " << (Fail ? "FAIL\n" : "PASS\n"));
5124 break;
5125 }
5126 case MCD::OPC_Fail: {
5127 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << Loc << ": OPC_Fail\n");
5128 return MCDisassembler::Fail;
5129 }
5130 }
5131 }
5132 llvm_unreachable("bogosity detected in disassembler state machine!");
5133}
